To get up and running, install simavr (command for debian bullseye):

    sudo apt-get install simavr libsimavr2 libsimavrparts1 libsimavr-dev libsimavr-examples

The simgui (running in a subprocess, spawned by simulator) requires tcl/tk.

Type `make' in this directory to build the firmware (with simulation
bits) and the simulator itself.

Make sure picocom is installed. Run the simulation:
    export SIMAVR_UART_XTERM=1
    ./simulator

Open the trace:
    gtkwave trace.vcd
